	<h3>Laptop Orchestra of Arizona State (LOrkAS)</h3>
	<p>The newly formed Laptop Orchestra of Arizona State (LOrkAS) welcomes you to our second public jam session. The undergraduate and graduate researchers of this ensemble, which is descended from the Princeton and Stanford LOrks, are beginning to push the envelope of integrating arts and technology into a trans-disciplinary entity. The ensemble serves as a one-of-a-kind learning environment where one can expand music, computer science, composition, movement, visuals, and live performance skills in a naturally interdisciplinary way. Come experience this uniquely immersive experience. Witness our next iteration as we begin to explore the answer to the question: 'What does it mean to be a laptop orchestra?'<br/><br/>
	This jam features original compositions by Perry Cook and Ge Wang from Stanford and Princeton, and by Scott Smallwood and Dan Trueman from Princeton.<br/></p>
